PN,42902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F429A1775056271
OL,3,CInquest to open into baby found under
OL,4,Cfloorboards during renovation
OL,6,FDurham Constabulary have previously
OL,7,Fsaid that forensic analysts believed
OL,8,Fthe full-term baby, which had twine
OL,9,Faround its neck, had lain undisturbed
OL,10,Fsince the early 20th century.
OL,12,FIn November 2024, the force said
OL,13,Fcarbon dating confirmed the skeleton
OL,14,Fdated to before 1955, aligning with
OL,15,Fdetectives' initial assumption that it
OL,16,Fcould be from around 1910.
OL,18,FInitial results of a DNA sample
OL,19,Findicated the baby was a boy.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/4
